<section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto w-full px-4 py-16 md:py-24">
	<h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-foreground mb-8">
		Convert Nikon Picture Controls to Lightroom Presets
	</h2>

	<div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
		<div class="glass-clear rounded-xl p-6">
			<h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-aurora-violet uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">NP3 = Nikon Picture Control</h3>
			<p class="text-sm text-foreground-muted leading-relaxed">
				Nikon's proprietary preset format used by the Z&nbsp;f, Z6III, Z8, Z9, and Z50II.
				Creative Picture Controls like Rich Tone Portrait, Flexible Color, and film emulations
				are stored as .np3 files.
			</p>
		</div>

		<div class="glass-clear rounded-xl p-6">
			<h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-aurora-cyan uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">XMP = Lightroom Preset</h3>
			<p class="text-sm text-foreground-muted leading-relaxed">
				Adobe's standard format for Lightroom Classic and Lightroom CC presets.
				Controls exposure, tone, color grading, HSL mixer, sharpening, and more.
			</p>
		</div>

		<div class="glass-clear rounded-xl p-6">
			<h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-aurora-soft-pink uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">Why Convert?</h3>
			<p class="text-sm text-foreground-muted leading-relaxed">
				48 parameters mapped automatically between NP3 and XMP.
				Free, private, instant. No uploads, no accounts.
				Take your in-camera look into post-processing — or bring your Lightroom style to your Nikon.
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>
